<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Ok..This is my point, I will bother to go down and kill these 2 mobs that are deemed worthless by NB and VoF, but by Virtue of the pointless rules that wont allow the 2 to be killed I cannot.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No you won’t actually, because if you could, you would be on rotation.  Guilds on ST rotation trying to get on Ancients rotation don’t kill the 3rd and 4th, and leave the first two up.  In fact, that would be quite an accomplishment of exploitive pulling, considering you would have to pull either the 1st or 2nd first to even get to the 3rd or 4th.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Yeah but that means there are 2 less Ancients spawned, so basically 2 mobs wasted. Which is part of my concern.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> Yeah but that means there are 2 less Ancients spawned, so basically 2 mobs wasted. Which is part of my concern.[/quote]<br>
<br>
Again, the 1-2 that are wasting are mobs “wasting” that if you could kill, you would already be on the rotation and not having this discussion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> VoF and NB are not intrested in killing 1-3 dragons, its all or not, and even with 4 up sometimes the mobs remain untouched for weeks.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
While it’s true VoF has been more active than we are on the Ancients rotation, what is your source of info that they are left up “for weeks at a time”.  You can’t track them from the zone in.  VoF from my understanding has been very active on killing the Ancients, and we go when we have enough people who need primal for us to go.  At 3 dragons, you are at the cusp of my interest, and you are right, I don’t feel like clearing all the way down to do the two hardest dragons for only 2-4 pieces of primal when I am looking for specific types.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Once the 4th dragon(AE slow) is killed by that guild add them to the rotation, the guild having to kill all 4 dragons in one clean sweep is also BS. MoTG/Prog can be killed in 2 seperate nights and you'll get a place on the ST rotation why is ancients any diffrent? If you can kill the 4th, you should be added to the rotation, I think the guild having done that has proven themsleves worthy of the rotation.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You have your info wrong Kenshirro.  If you only kill MotG one night, the Prog won’t be up the next night for you to do him.  No guild on the rotation is going to kill Prog and leave MotG up either, just like no one is going to kill the two hard dragons and leave the two easy ones up.  The rules work, kill all four dragons, on your ST turn, and welcome to the rotation.  Don’t snipe mobs that you aren’t on rotation for – it’s no different than killing Ikky and Eashen when you can’t kill Roy.  It hinders the guilds on the Ancients rotation from doing their mobs.<br>
<br>
<br>
Kelon,<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> What would this mean for the guilds on rotation? Nothing at all. If people went in one day after the rotation guild is done, then the full respawn will be up if and when you decide to take your turn.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
